Subject: [PATCH 0864/1594] MLK-10347 IMX6SX: EPDC: refine a variable
 definition to avoid potential risk

commit 0c9704f8f158338bcb4c27f3d707c15e4ff78a8f from
git://git.freescale.com/imx/linux-2.6-imx.git

Modify the 'hard_lock' variable to be static to avoid
potential name conflict with other kernel modules.

Signed-off-by: Fancy Fang <chen.fang@freescale.com>
---
 drivers/video/fbdev/mxc/mxc_epdc_fb.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/video/fbdev/mxc/mxc_epdc_fb.c b/drivers/video/fbdev/mxc/mxc_epdc_fb.c
index f6be90d..472f726 100644
--- a/drivers/video/fbdev/mxc/mxc_epdc_fb.c
+++ b/drivers/video/fbdev/mxc/mxc_epdc_fb.c
@@ -90,7 +90,7 @@
 #define MERGE_BLOCK	2
 
 static unsigned long default_bpp = 16;
-DEFINE_MUTEX(hard_lock);
+static DEFINE_MUTEX(hard_lock);
 
 struct update_marker_data {
 	struct list_head full_list;
